President Donald Trump is requesting that Congress extend trade authorities procedures for three years. He states that his administration has made progress in trade negotiations and the extension is necessary. Trump emphasizes his administration's commitment to using the leverage of the largest economy to open foreign markets and obtain fair treatment for American workers. He mentions the renegotiation of the North American Free Trade Agreement and exploring potential trade agreement partners in Africa and Southeast Asia. Trump hopes to work with Congress to pursue new and better trade deals for American workers, farmers, ranchers, and businesses, and believes that the extension of trade authorities procedures is essential to demonstrate a common goal with trading partners.